               <msContents>
                  <summary>Account in grain. It mentions the private teacher (kathegetes) Harpokration, probably the Valerius Harpokration who was the author of the Lexicon of the Ten Orators. It also includes Fronto the rhetor, perhaps the tutor of Marcus Aurelius. The account includes payments to Paean chanters (paianistai)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back another text quite effaced in a small hand</note>
                     <note type="general">At least 20 lines, broken on all sides</note>
                     <note type="general">Small, even hand a bit bent to the right</note>
                     <note type="general">Paean chanters are usually associated with festivities of various kind</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
